From 5ad615607b71884fb46d9a82ec03a737262276b5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keshav Gupta <keshavg@marvell.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 20:54:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] [sonic-yang-mgmt] Fix port breakout failure due to unhandled
 empty CABLE_LENGTH|AZURE dict

Problem:
On a system where all ports are breakout-capable, if we break out ports
one by one, the breakout fails for the last port with the error below:

root@sonic:/home/admin# sudo config interface breakout Ethernet112 "2x400G[200G,100G]" -y -f
Running Breakout Mode : 1x800G[400G,200G]
Target Breakout Mode : 2x400G[200G,100G]

Ports to be deleted :
 {
     "Ethernet112": "800000"
}
Ports to be added :
 {
     "Ethernet112": "400000",
     "Ethernet116": "400000"
}
sonic_yang(3):Get Data Tree Failed:'CABLE_LENGTH'
Get Data Tree Failed
'CABLE_LENGTH'
Port Deletion Failed
[ERROR] Port breakout Failed!!! Opting Out
Failed to break out Port. Error:
root@sonic:/home/admin#

This error occurs because removing dependent configuration leaves
the CABLE_LENGTH|AZURE dict empty, which causes two failures:

1. _xlateType1MapList: An empty inner dict produces an empty YANG list
   that libyang rejects as invalid JSON during data loading.

2. _revXlateType1MapList: After YANG validation, accessing
   entry[inner_clist['@name']] raises a KeyError when the inner list
   has been removed, preventing reverse translation back to config DB.

Fix:
- In _xlateType1MapList: skip and remove config entries with empty
  inner dicts before attempting YANG list conversion.
- In _revXlateType1MapList: use dict.get() to safely check for the
  inner list and skip entries where it is missing or empty, avoiding
  KeyError and preventing empty hashes in config DB.

Signed-off-by: Keshav Gupta <keshavg@marvell.com>
---
 src/sonic-yang-mgmt/sonic_yang_ext.py | 13 +++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sonic-yang-mgmt/sonic_yang_ext.py b/src/sonic-yang-mgmt/sonic_yang_ext.py
index 30de8c32c..9c6537c98 100644
--- a/src/sonic-yang-mgmt/sonic_yang_ext.py
+++ b/src/sonic-yang-mgmt/sonic_yang_ext.py
@@ -582,6 +582,12 @@ class SonicYangExtMixin(SonicYangPathMixin):
         primaryKeys = list(config.keys())
         for pkey in primaryKeys:
             try:
+                # An empty inner dict would produce an empty YANG list which
+                # libyang rejects as invalid JSON.
+                if not config[pkey]:
+                    del config[pkey]
+                    continue
+
                 vKey = None
                 self.sysLog(syslog.LOG_DEBUG, "xlateList Extract pkey:{}".\
                     format(pkey))
@@ -972,9 +978,12 @@ class SonicYangExtMixin(SonicYangPathMixin):
                 # create key of config DB table
                 pkey, pkeydict = self._createKey(entry, listKeys)
                 self.sysLog(syslog.LOG_DEBUG, "revXlateList pkey:{}".format(pkey))
-                config[pkey]= dict()
                 # fill rest of the entries
-                inner_list = entry[inner_clist['@name']]
+                inner_list = entry.get(inner_clist['@name'])
+                # Inner list may not exist if all its entries were deleted
+                if not inner_list:
+                    continue
+                config[pkey]= dict()
                 for index in range(len(inner_list)):
                     self.sysLog(syslog.LOG_DEBUG, "revXlateList fkey:{} fval {}".\
                          format(str(inner_list[index][inner_listKey]),\
-- 
